Sentencas: One step method was investigated to prepare La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta-Ce0.80Gd0.2O2-delta (LSCFN-CGO) compound symmetrical electrode.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ Symmetrical Electrode for SOFC Performance Study

Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O3-delta (LSGM) was used as electrolyte and symmetrical cells with a configuration of LSCFN-CGO parallel to LSGM parallel to HLSCFN-CGO were fabricated.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ Symmetrical Electrode for SOFC Performance Study

Sentencas: Phase -analysis and electrode microstructure of LSCFN-CGO were examined by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Co-synthesis of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ Symmetrical Electrode for SOFC Performance Study

Sentencas: Results show that LSCFN-CGO is identified to be pure phase and perovskite structured LSCFN is chemically compatible with fluorite structured CGO.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ Symmetrical Electrode for SOFC Performance Study

Sentencas: With H-2 (3% H2O) and C3118 (3% H2O) as fuel for the cell, the maximum power densities are 980 and 869 mW/cm(2) at 850 degrees C. Moreover, the long-term stability of the cell is stable at constant current of 0.3 A/cm2 for 420 h with C3H8 (3% H2O) as fuel, 8 redox cycles are carried out, and the symmetrical electrode had ideal redox regeneration ability under carbon-based fuel.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ Symmetrical Electrode for SOFC Performance Study

Sentencas: The results show that one step method is a facile and optimized electrode fabrication procedure and owns promising application prospects.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ Symmetrical Electrode for SOFC Performance Study
